post_text:
Hello everyone! I hope everyone is healthy and doing well through the first month of school closure. We are halfway through the school closure to the end of the scheduled school year. I would again like to express the importance OF doing as much of the assigned work/activities you possibly can. Even though it is voluntary and not graded, the staff is sharing it with you to help keep your mind sharp & your brain engaged in your education and on-going learning.

This time is very unfortunate for everyone and I want you to know that all the employees at school miss you and want you to know that we are thinking about you and want what is best for you. You may email or call to reach us, as we are still here to help and support you. We will be sending information out about class registration and graduation later this week.

Stay healthy and stay BV Strong.

Mr. Brosamle

post_text: 8th grader Anna Seuntjens has been accepted into the 2019 OPUS All-State MS Honor Choir! To put it into perspective - 2630 students auditioned for one of 720 spots (a 28% acceptance rate). This is a big deal for her! She worked very hard to achieve this outstanding honor, so if you see her, PLEASE offer her a well deserved congratulations for her hard work!
